verbose_text: The available studies in mammals indicate that neither saturated fatty acids like palmitate (C16 :0) nor the presence of two (such as in linoleate, C18 :2 n-6) or three (such as in docosahexanoate, C22 :6 n-3) double bonds activate fatty acid sensing systems.
